        <description>
           The L’LORRI instrument provides the highest-resolution 
           imaging for the Lucy mission. The panchromatic images will
           address seven of our 17 Level 1 science requirements including
           searching for satellites, determining
           the size frequency distribution of craters, stereo imaging, and
           shape reconstruction. The L’LORRI instrument will also be
           used for optical navigation to our targets.
        </description>
